': \"You've guided me through challenges I couldn't face alone\", 'right': \"Your wisdom has been invaluable to my growth\", 'bottom': \"Thank you for investing your time, energy, and knowledge in me. You've helped me become who I am today, and I'm deeply grateful.\" }, { 'left': \"You believed in me before I believed in myself\", 'right': \"That confidence gave me the courage to keep going\", 'bottom': \"Thank you for seeing my potential, for challenging me to reach it, and for walking beside me on this journey. You've changed my life.\" } ], 'CAREGIVER': [ { 'left': \"You care for others with such grace and compassion\", 'right': \"That kind of heart is truly extraordinary\", 'bottom': \"Thank you for your patience, your kindness, and your tireless dedication. You make such a difference in the lives you touch every day.\" }, { 'left': \"You show up every day with love and dedication\", 'right': \"Even when the work is hard and thankless\", 'bottom': \"Thank you for everything you do. Your care, your compassion, and your commitment don't go unnoticed. You are deeply appreciated and valued.\" } ], } print(\"Starting comprehensive fix of all 500 cards...\") print(f\"Original word averages - Area3: {df['Area3_LeftSide'].astype(str).apply(lambda x: len(x.split())).mean():.1f}, Area4: {df['Area4_RightSide'].astype(str).apply(lambda x: len(x.split())).mean():.1f}, Area5: {df['Area5_FinalThoughts'].astype(str).apply(lambda x: len(x.split())).mean():.1f}\") # Fix all cards for idx, row in df.iterrows(): relationship = row['Area2_Relationship'].upper().strip() # Get message set for this relationship if relationship in RELATIONSHIP_MESSAGES: messages = RELATIONSHIP_MESSAGES[relationship] selected = random.choice(messages) df.at[idx, 'Area3_LeftSide'] = selected['left'] df.at[idx, 'Area4_RightSide'] = selected['right'] df.at[idx, 'Area5_FinalThoughts'] = selected['bottom'] else: # Generic fallback for any relationships not in library df.at[idx, 'Area3_LeftSide'] = \"You've made such a difference in my life\" df.at[idx, 'Area4_RightSide'] = \"And I'm grateful for you every single day\" df.at[idx, 'Area5_FinalThoughts'] = \"Thank you for being exactly who you are. Your presence in my life is a gift I'll always treasure and appreciate.\" # Verify no problematic phrases remain learning_check = df['Area4_RightSide'].astype(str).str.contains('Our still learning', case=False, na=False).sum() never_a3 = df['Area3_LeftSide'].astype(str).str.contains('Never forget', case=False, na=False).sum() never_a4 = df['Area4_RightSide'].astype(str).str.contains('Never forget', case=False, na=False).sum() never_a5 = df['Area5_FinalThoughts'].astype(str).str.contains('Never forget', case=False, na=False).sum() print(f\"\\n✓ Problematic phrase removal:\") print(f\" 'Our still learning' remaining: {learning_check}\") print(f\" 'Never forget' in Area3: {never_a3}\") print(f\" 'Never forget' in Area4: {never_a4}\") print(f\" 'Never forget' in Area5: {never_a5}\") # Check new word counts new_area3_avg = df['Area3_LeftSide'].astype(str).apply(lambda x: len(x.split())).mean() new_area4_avg = df['Area4_RightSide'].astype(str).apply(lambda x: len(x.split())).mean() new_area5_avg = df['Area5_FinalThoughts'].astype(str).apply(lambda x: len(x.split())).mean() print(f\"\\n✓ New word distribution:\") print(f\" Area3_LeftSide: {new_area3_avg:.1f} words (target: 7-10)\") print(f\" Area4_RightSide: {new_area4_avg:.1f} words (target: 7-10)\") print(f\" Area5_FinalThoughts: {new_area5_avg:.1f} words (target: 18-25)\") # Save final file output_file = 'TAB4_CANVA_PUBLICATION_READY.csv' df.to_csv(output_file, index=False) print(f\"\\n✓ Saved publication-ready file: {output_file}\") print(f\" Total cards: {len(df)}\") # Show examples print(\"\\n=== SAMPLE FIXED CARDS ===\\n\") for i in [0, 133, 224, 297]: # Show previously problematic cards row = df.iloc[i] print(f\"Card {i+1}: {row['Area2_Relationship']}\") print(f\" LEFT: {row['Area3_LeftSide']}\") print(f\" RIGHT: {row['Area4_RightSide']}\") print(f\" BOTTOM: {row['Area5_FinalThoughts']}\") print() SCRIPT_END View Starting comprehensive fix of all 500 cards... Original word averages - Area3: 11.5, Area4: 12.2, Area5: 25.1 ... LEFT: You are strong, capable, and deeply loved RIGHT: I'm so proud of the man you're becoming BOTTOM: Thank you for being exactly who you are. Remember that it's okay to feel, to struggle, and to ask for help. I'... Exit Code: 0 Perfect! Now let me verify the quality and create a final grammar check to ensure everything is publication-ready: Using Tool | Bash Command cd /home/user && python3 << 'SCRIPT_END' import pandas as pd df = pd.read_csv('TAB4_CANVA_PUBLICATION_READY.csv') print(\"=== FINAL QUALITY VERIFICATION ===\\n\") # 1. Check for any remaining problematic phrases problematic_phrases = [ 'Our still learning', 'Never forget', 'is growing together', 'transcends typical', 'The day you boyfriend' ] print(\"1. PROBLEMATIC PHRASE CHECK:\") all_clear = True for phrase in problematic_phrases: count_a3 = df['Area3_LeftSide'].astype(str).str.contains(phrase, case=False, na=False).sum() count_a4 = df['Area4_RightSide'].astype(str).str.contains(phrase, case=False, na=False).sum() count_a5 = df['Area5_FinalThoughts'].astype(str).str.contains(phrase, case=False, na=False).sum() total = count_a3 + count_a4 + count_a5 if total > 0: print(f\" ⚠ '{phrase}': {total} instances found\") all_clear = False if all_clear: print(\" ✓ All problematic phrases removed\") # 2. Word count distribution print(\"\\n2. WORD COUNT DISTRIBUTION:\") df['a3_words'] = df['Area3_LeftSide'].astype(str).apply(lambda x: len(x.split())) df['a4_words'] = df['Area4_RightSide'].astype(str).apply(lambda x: len(x.split())) df['a5_words'] = df['Area5_FinalThoughts'].astype(str).apply(lambda x: len(x.split())) print(f\" Area3_LeftSide: {df['a3_words'].mean():.1f} avg, {df['a3_words'].min()}-{df['a3_words'].max()} range\") print(f\" Area4_RightSide: {df['a4_words'].mean():.1f} avg, {df['a4_words'].min()}-{df['a4_words'].max()} range\") print(f\" Area5_FinalThoughts: {df['a5_words'].mean():.1f} avg, {df['a5_words'].min()}-{df['a5_words'].max()} range\") # 3. Check for incomplete sentences or fragments print(\"\\n3. GRAMMAR CHECK (Sentence Structure):\") incomplete_count = 0 for col in ['Area3_LeftSide', 'Area4_RightSide', 'Area5_FinalThoughts']: for idx, text in df[col].items(): text_str = str(text).strip() # Very basic checks - no single words, must have verb-like patterns if len(text_str.split()) == 1: print(f\" ⚠ Single word in {col} row {idx}: {text_str}\") incomplete_count += 1 if incomplete_count == 0: p"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"[Content truncated — view full chat at source URL]"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"Source: "},{"type":"link","href":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=e348d3e4-2ba1-46cb-aeb8-7e4f318b0590","children":[{"text":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=e348d3e4-2ba1-46cb-aeb8-7e4f318b0590"}]}]}]
